timeline.bodyText:
Instead of doing this, I think it would be better to do something like this:
protected void handleNames(Criteria criteria, StringAndListParam name, StringAndListParam given, StringAndListParam family) {
    return handleNames(criteria, name, given, family, null);
}

protected void handleNames(Criteria criteria, StringAndListParam name, StringAndListParam given, StringAndListParam family, String personAlias) {
    if (name == null & given == null && family == null) {
        return;
    }

    if (StringUtils.isNotBlank(personAlias) {
        criteria.createAlias(String.format("%.names", personAlias), "pn");
    } else {
        criteria.createAlias("names", "pn");
    }

    ...
}
This doesn't break existing code and, to me, at any rate personAlias tells me what that parameter is and why it's important more than isInnerQuery does.

